                        tv_Lang.setText(getString(R.string.persian));
                        tv_Head.setText(getString(R.string.tv_Thealchemist));
                        tv_Text.setText("Once upon a time, there was a young shepherd named Santiago who lived in Andalusia, a region in Spain. Despite leading a simple life, Santiago had a deep desire to explore the world and discover his personal legend—a term referring to one’s true purpose in life.\n" +
                                "\n" + "One night, Santiago had a recurring dream about a hidden treasure in the Egyptian pyramids. Intrigued and eager to pursue his destiny, he decided to leave his flock and set off on an extraordinary journey to find the treasure. Along the way, he met an old king named Melchizedek, who advised him to listen to his heart and follow the omens that the universe presents.\n" +
                                "\n" + "As Santiago embarked on his adventure, he encountered a series of encounters and lessons that shaped his character and deepened his understanding of life. He met an Englishman who sought the knowledge of alchemy, a mystical discipline focused on transforming ordinary metals into gold. The Englishman shared his desire to find a legendary alchemist living in the desert.\n" +
                                "\n" + "Santiago’s journey continued, and he eventually reached an oasis in the middle of the desert. It was there that he met an enchanting woman named Fatima, with whom he fell in love. Despite his strong feelings for Fatima, he knew he had to continue his quest for the treasure. The Alchemist, a wise man, joined Santiago in his journey and taught him valuable lessons about following one’s dreams and listening to the Soul of the World.\n" +
                                "\n" + "Together, Santiago and the Alchemist traversed the treacherous desert. Throughout their journey, the Alchemist imparted wisdom to Santiago, teaching him about the interconnectedness of all things and the importance of listening to his heart. Santiago also learned the principle of the Personal Legend, the concept that everyone has a unique destiny that they must pursue with unwavering determination.\n" +
                                "\n" + "Finally, Santiago and the Alchemist arrived at the Egyptian pyramids, the location of the hidden treasure. However, their journey was not without obstacles. As they approached the pyramids, they were captured by a group of warriors. Santiago’s life hung in the balance, and the only way he could save himself was by turning the lead of his heart into gold, showcasing the true power of alchemy.\n" +
                                "\n" + "In a climactic turn of events, Santiago realized that the treasure he had been searching for was not actually located at the pyramids. Instead, it was buried in the place where his journey had started—his homeland. The true treasure was the personal growth, knowledge, and experiences he gained throughout his pilgrimage.\n" +
                                "\n" + "Returning home, Santiago unearthed the treasure he had left behind and discovered that his love for Fatima had remained true. They embraced and vowed to build a life together. The story ends with Santiago understanding the significance of following one’s dreams, listening to one’s heart, and appreciating the journey itself.\n" +
                                "\n" + "“The Alchemist,” written by Paulo Coelho, is a timeless tale that captures the essence of personal growth, self-discovery, and the pursuit of one’s dreams. It teaches children (and adults) that the true treasure lies not in material wealth but in the lessons learned and the transformation experienced on the journey towards realizing their personal legends.\n");
