////                        tv_Text.setText("Once upon a time in Afghanistan, there lived a young boy named Amir. He had a close friend named Hassan, who was like a brother to him. Amir and Hassan loved to fly kites together in the blue sky, and their favorite kite-fighting tournament was coming up.\n\n        But something troubled Amir. He felt guilty about a terrible event that happened years ago when he didn't stand up for Hassan, his loyal friend. This regret weighed heavy on his heart.\n\nAmir's father, Baba, was a strong and respected man in their community. He always encouraged Amir to be brave and stand up for what was right. However, Amir couldn't find the courage to make things right with Hassan.\n\nOne day, during the kite-fighting tournament, something terrible happened. Amir won the tournament, and everyone celebrated his victory. But as Amir searched for Hassan to share the joy, he found him trapped and facing a group of bullies. Amir could have helped Hassan, but fear paralyzed him, and he ran away.\n\nThe guilt consumed Amir, and he couldn't face Hassan anymore. Eventually, circumstances forced Amir and his father to leave Afghanistan and seek refuge in America. The memories of his childhood and the unfulfilled friendship haunted him even in this new land.\n\nYears passed, and one day, Amir received a phone call from an old family friend, Rahim Khan. Rahim Khan revealed a secret that changed everything. He told Amir about Hassan's fate and a chance for redemption.\n\nAmir learned that Hassan had a son named Sohrab, who was in grave danger in Afghanistan. Amir's heart was torn between his past mistakes and the opportunity to make amends. He realized that he had to be brave like his father had taught him and face his fears.\n\n        Amir embarked on a journey back to his homeland to rescue Sohrab. The war-torn Afghanistan he found was a stark contrast to the peaceful place he remembered. But he was determined to find Sohrab and right his wrongs.\n\n        Amir encountered many challenges and dangers in his quest to find Sohrab. He faced ruthless men who were involved in terrible deeds. But Amir's love for his friend's son gave him strength, and he refused to give up.\n\nFinally, Amir found Sohrab, but he was in a terrible situation. The cruel man who held him captive was none other than Amir's childhood enemy, Assef. Amir had to face his fears once again and fight for Sohrab's freedom.\n\nIn a brave and fierce battle, Amir confronted Assef and rescued Sohrab. But the journey wasn't over yet. Sohrab was deeply scarred by the suffering he endured, and Amir was determined to bring him to a better life in America.\n\nBack in America, Amir and Sohrab faced new challenges in adjusting to their new life. But they had each other, and gradually, their wounds started to heal. Amir's heart was finally at peace, and he knew he had found his redemption.\n\n\"The Kite Runner\" is a powerful tale of friendship, forgiveness, and bravery. It teaches us that mistakes can be made, but we have the strength to make amends and change our destiny. Amir's journey shows that true courage comes from facing our fears and standing up for what is right, even when it seems impossible. And most importantly, it reminds us of the enduring power of friendship and the healing nature of love.");
